Implement the public `insert_list/3` function.

`insert_list(count, name, overrides)` persists `count` structs for the named
factory `name` (each with the given `overrides`) and returns the list of
persisted structs, in order. It is guarded so that `count` is a non-negative
integer. Insertion must run **concurrently** — spawn one `Task` per record via
`Task.async/1`, each calling `insert(name, overrides)`, then collect the results
with `Task.await_many/1`. Because each record is built inside its own task, every
sequence-driven value and every assigned id stays unique across the list. A
`count` of `0` must return `[]` (an empty range produces no tasks).

